.TH AVC-PARSER 1 "March 2026" "avc-parser 1.8.1" "SELinux Policy Tools"
.SH NAME
avc-parser \- SELinux AVC denial parser and analyzer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B avc-parser
.RB [ \-f
.IR FILE ]
.RB [ \-\-json ]
.RB [ \-\-report
.RB { brief | sealert }]
.RB [ \-\-process
.IR NAME ]
.RB [ \-\-source
.IR TYPE ]
.RB [ \-\-target
.IR TYPE ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B avc-parser
parses SELinux AVC denial messages from audit logs with support for
extended audit records (SYSCALL, PATH, CWD, PROCTITLE). Provides smart
deduplication, severity classification, and multiple output formats.
.PP
Auto-detects raw audit.log vs pre-processed ausearch format.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS "Input Options"
.TP
.BI \-f " FILE" "\fR, \fP" \-\-file " FILE"
Path to audit file (auto-detects format).
.TP
.BI \-rf " FILE" "\fR, \fP" \-\-raw\-file " FILE"
Path to raw audit.log file.
.TP
.BI \-af " FILE" "\fR, \fP" \-\-avc\-file " FILE"
Path to pre-processed ausearch output.
.SS "Display Options"
.TP
.B \-\-json
Output in JSON format (for tool integration).
.TP
.B \-\-fields
Field-by-field technical breakdown.
.TP
.B \-\-detailed
Detailed view with per-PID timestamps and syscalls.
.TP
.BI \-\-report " FORMAT"
Report format: \fBbrief\fR (executive summary) or \fBsealert\fR (technical).
.TP
.B \-\-pager
Use interactive pager for large outputs.
.SS "Filtering Options"
.TP
.BI \-\-process " NAME"
Filter by process name.
.TP
.BI \-\-path " PATH"
Filter by file path (supports wildcards).
.TP
.BI \-\-source " TYPE"
Filter by source SELinux context type.
.TP
.BI \-\-target " TYPE"
Filter by target SELinux context type.
.TP
.BI \-\-since " TIME"
Only include denials since this time.
.TP
.BI \-\-until " TIME"
Only include denials until this time.
.SS "Sorting Options"
.TP
.BI \-\-sort " ORDER"
Sort order: \fBrecent\fR (default), \fBcount\fR, or \fBchrono\fR.
.SS "Advanced Options"
.TP
.B \-\-legacy\-signatures
Use legacy 4-tuple signatures for deduplication (for regression comparison).
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose debug output to stderr.
.TP
.B \-\-stats
Show aggregate statistics summary instead of individual denials.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
# Parse audit log with brief report
avc-parser \-f /var/log/audit/audit.log \-\-report brief

# JSON output for tool integration
avc-parser \-f /var/log/audit/audit.log \-\-json

# Filter by httpd denials
avc-parser \-f /var/log/audit/audit.log \-\-process httpd

# Recent denials only
avc-parser \-f /var/log/audit/audit.log \-\-since "1 hour ago"
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sepgen (1),
.BR semacro (1),
.BR ausearch (8),
.BR audit2allow (1),
.BR semanage (8)
